YENAGOA – Ijaw youths under the auspices of the Ijaw Youths Council (IYC) have conferred an award of Grand Ambassador of the IYC on the Bayelsa State Governor, Douye Diri. The IYC President, Peter Igbifa, led members of his executive council to give Diri a letter of credence confirming the award bestowed on him at the Government House, Yenagoa, at the weekend. Speaking, Igbifa called on politicians of Ijaw extraction to close ranks and work in unity to develop Bayelsa. Osun Guber: Let’s Close Ranks And Eschew Bitterness,… Enugu 2023: Ugwanyi, Nwobodo, Nwodo, Nnamani, Chime Back Enugu… He applauded Diri for his commitment to the development and progress of the state and indeed the Ijaw nation, describing his leadership style as outstanding. Igbifa said, “We have decided to confer on you the Grand Ambassador of IYC for your outstanding and credible leadership style. You have shown love and commitment to develop the Ijaw nation. “You have also worked for the unity of this nation beyond party lines and that is why we are calling on all politicians in Ijaw land to close ranks and work in unity despite their party affiliations for the progress of Ijaw nation. They need to join you to spread the love because we must put a winnable plan in motion to achieve a prosperous nation”. In his remarks while receiving the award, Governor Diri thanked the Ijaw youth leader for the recognition and commended him for changing the narrative in IYC. He described the letter of credence as a strategic gesture and a huge encouragement for him to do more. POLL The Bayelsa governor said, “This goes to show that the only way for Ijaw nation is progress and that the face of the Ijaw nation is up again. This is the first of credence written by a renowned youth organisation in the recent times”.